Simple CNC Turning Program Example
O1001
G21        (Metric units)
G90        (Absolute programming)
G00 X50 Z5 (Rapid move to start position)

G01 X40 Z0 F0.2  (Start cutting)
G01 Z-30         (Turning along Z axis)

G00 X60 Z10      (Retract tool)

M30              (End program)
🔹 Explanation of Common Codes
Code	Meaning
G00	Rapid tool movement
G01	Linear cutting movement
G02	Clockwise arc cutting
G03	Counter-clockwise arc
G21	Metric units
G90	Absolute positioning
M03	Spindle ON (clockwise)
M05	Spindle OFF
M30	End of program
🔹 Example: Facing Operation
O2001
G21
G90
M03 S1000

G00 X50 Z2
G01 X0 F0.2

G00 X50 Z5
M05
M30

This program faces the front surface of the workpiece.
